<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Looting from Containers - TheBlack</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?The RealmWeaver">The RealmWeaver</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 1:08 p.m. 11/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Looting from Containers - TheBlack<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>I agree wholeheartedly with every single one of your suggestions except the container looting. I think players should have the opportunity, realistic or not, to preserve an item or two of their choice before they meet their ultimate doom. I think it is incredibly discouraging and very dishertening to know that, without a doubt, hands down, if you die you will lose the best item on your body. If you die again, the second best, etc. Right now, you might want this implemented because people only have one or two nice items. That half-elf with the magic chainmail, the wizard with the magical dagger, etc. However, as time progresses and people begin to outfit themselves with entire suits of valuable, rare items, then this will no longer be a problem. The player will be able to choose ONE or TWO items to put in a backpack, given the time they have between attack and death, and you will also get a nice item for killing them. The fact is, EverQuest is NOT like any other online game in the past, because these items can take literally weeks of real time playing to get. A person who FINALLY after working for weeks to achieve, gets a rare item does not like to know that the first time he dies it is gone, regardless of how fast he puts it in a container. Realism aside, and greedy gang PKers aside, players SHOULD have the opporunity to preserve one or two of their favorite items from grubby little punks who would kill them on site just for the platinum their weapon would draw.

<P>P.S. - I know ten of you want to click the reply button and write "Then go to a different server." I know, I've heard it before. It goes like this. "Please improve the PVP server, it needs work." - "Then go to a different server BIIAAATCH." Please refrain, I will imagine I read your post.
<P>[Realmwevaer]
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
